	   <tr><td colspan=2>I don't get it. Why do we have to be sorry and find excuses for those who don't get it? A bard is a bard.<br>A warrior is only a half bard because he doesn't have any idea about singing. Ok, he slashes... how boring.<br>A magican is only half bard because he can't defend himself. Ok, he knows some spells... but helpless on his own.<br>A ranger, a rogue ... oh, a bard is that as well.<br>There are tons of "half" bards around... go for the real one. (But maybe some people have the need to concentrate on a "single" ability... )<br>May your songs never end!<br><br>Wara "Merry Fairytune"<br>Wood Elf Bard<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
