	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jun 25th 11:16 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Songs fizzle if you aren't skilled in the particular instrument type of the song you are trying to sing (even if you aren't trying to use an instrument).&nbsp;&nbsp;For example, if you haven't trained up your brass skill by using a brass instrument, Denon's Disruptive Dischord will fizzle about 80% of the time.<br><br>The easiest way to train up these skills is to grab the appropriate instrument, find a quiet corner and just set your character to sing one song.<br><br>Hope that helps.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
