	   <tr><td colspan=2>I play a half elf bard.&nbsp;&nbsp;The reasons that I picked this race are a) good starting locations (picked Qeynos myself) b) stats are fair and night vision c) they look cool in any armor.  Hide and forage skills are acquired later in levels anyway so I dont think you should worry to much about these skills.  Someone else will have to help you with a deity because I have none. The bottom line is that I have had the most fun with this character class then any of the others that I have played.  You can solo pretty well, you are always a welcome addition to groups, and you can run like Forrest Gump. When you create this character I would suggest getting your charisma to 103, your dexterity (for songs) and strength (carry that armor) as high as possible (get items that help here). Peace out.<br><br>Windracer<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
