<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99236764082924></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99236764082924><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99236764082924>RE: keyboard set-ups</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99236764082924#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=18289><span id= >djgibson</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>13 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jun 12th 1:40 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Don't know if this is best but it is what I do.&nbsp;&nbsp;I use the keys around 's' on the keyboard from movement (w=forward, d = right, a = left, x = back)- I use s to center view, I use e to look up and v to look down (would rather have c but keep that for consider).  <br>What all this does is it allows me to use left hand to control all movement and keep my right hand on the mouse.  My left hand is kept in a natural touch typing position.  This way I can target someone/something or click on the song icons with the mouse.  I also have F1-F6 for party and F8 for NPC and F9 to change views (useful during running with party or getting an overhead view during fights or kiting when soloing).  <br><br>Hope that helps.<br><br>Mahew Ravenheart<br>51 Minstrel, Xev<br>&nbsp;<br>Mahew Ravenheart<br>51 Minstrel, Xev</td></tr>
